incidents.title: New Release from Beck "Unevetful Days (Radio Edit)" On Capitol Records

details.emailBody:
"

Listen Now
Artist Title Time
Beck Unevetful Days (Radio Edit) 02:59

BECK

“UNEVENTFUL DAYS”

(2:59 – RADIO EDIT)

 

Officially IMPACTING AAA: October 28th

Available For Adds & Airplay: NOW

***

 

HYPERSPACE

14th ALBUM OUT NOVEMBER 22 ON CAPITOL RECORDS

NEW SINGLE “UNEVENTFUL DAYS” INCLUDED WITH ALL PRE-ORDERS

 

Electric life will be in all our brains November 22, when Capitol Records releases Hyperspace: new colors, next phase and the brand new 14th album from seven-time GRAMMY-winning cultural chameleon BECK.

 

Hyperspace’s new dimensions in sound are the result of Beck’s most collaborative efforts to date. Seven of the album's 11 tracks—including single “Uneventful Days” and “Saw Lightning” (as featured in the Beats by Dr. Dre Powerbeats Pro campaign and also included with pre-orders)—feature co-writing and co-production from Pharrell Williams. Elsewhere in Hyperspace, “See Through” is co-written/co-produced by frequent Beck collaborator Greg Kurstin, “Star” is co-written/co-produced by Paul Epworth, “Stratosphere” features back-up from Chris Martin, the album’s title track features guest vocals from Terrell Hines, and “Die Waiting” is co-written/co-produced by Cole M.G.N. with backing vocals from Sky Ferreira. Longtime Beck bandmates Jason Falkner, Smokey Hormel and Roger Manning Jr. feature on much of the album as well.

 

The complete track listing for Hyperspace is:

            1. Hyperlife

            2. Uneventful Days

            3. Saw Lightning

            4. Die Waiting

            5. Chemical

            6. See Through

            7. Hyperspace

            8. Stratosphere

            9. Dark Places

            10. Star

            11. Everlasting Nothing

 

Hyperspace will be Beck’s first album since 2017’s Colors, which won Best Alternative Music Album and Best Engineered Album, Non-Classical at the 61st GRAMMY Awards earlier this year. Beck's prolific post-Colors/pre-Hyperspace output has included “Tarantula” from Music Inspired by ROMA, “Super Cool” (featuring Robyn & The Lonely Island) from The LEGO Movie 2, and his feature appearance on Cage The Elephant’s “Night Running”—not to mention roadwork ranging from this summer’s co-headlining amphitheater tour with Cage The Elephant to his 2018 debut headline at Madison Square Garden to a stint as special guest on U2’s The Joshua Tree 2017 Tour.

###

incidents.title: Introducing Somi Arian, as a Potential Speaker & Educator

details.emailBody:
"

Hi Neele

I'm writing to introduce our Founder, Somi Arian, as a potential speaker for your events, as I believe her profile could be of interest to you.

Somi is a Filmmaker, and Tech Philosopher, who has conducted an in-depth study about the impact of disruptive technologies on modern society. Somi's research has broad applications to areas of marketing, human resources, mental health, and diversity, to name a few. She also has a unique backstory which makes well placed as an inspirational speaker.

Somi has now been commissioned to write a book on "the future of work". Her documentary, "The Millennial Disruption", has won multiple awards in international film festivals and earned her the LinkedIn Top Voice award. You can access the film here:

http://smartcookiemedia.com/doc

As an industry leader, Somi has a large following on LinkedIn. As a speaker, Somi is highly engaging and memorable. She has given keynote speeches for large corporations and international conferences, such as Legal Week, Morgan Stanley, and AdWeek, to name a few. Here is a link to Somi's speaker reel:

http://smartcookiemedia.com/book-somi-arian/

Should you wish to have Somi as a speaker at your future events, please let me know so we may arrange a call to discuss further details.

Kind regards,

------

Lola Ortiz

Head of Market Research

Smart Cookie Media

Website | LinkedIn

+44 7947 280596

incidents.title: Can’t make it to ONWARD19? Watch it live!
Private Health Insurance Development in France——French Prudential Supervision and Resolution Authority (ACPR)

details.emailBody:
"
如果邮件不能正常显示，请点击此处

分享到:  


World Health Insurance Innovation Congress 2020
January 15-16th | London, UK
Innovation for Growth and Protection
 
 
What is the Prospects of Private Health Insurance Development in France?

In France, people obtain basic health insurance coverage through a public health insurance system. Although public coverage is comprehensive, substantial co-payments and deductibles are more and more required and individuals become increasingly dependent on private complementary health insurance, to be better reimbursed. In the context of strengthened constraints to control public health spending, the market for complementary cover is indeed likely to develop. This expansion has several implications for the regulation of private health insurance.

As a congress focusing on global health insurance, we has invited Mr. Bernard DELAS, who is the Vice President of French Prudential Supervision and Resolution Authority (ACPR, the French supervisory authority of the banking and insurance sector.) to attend World Health Insurance Innovation Congress 2020. Join us to see The Prospects of Private Health Insurance Development in France from Mr. Bernard!
 

Bernard Delas
Vice President
French Prudential Supervision and Resolution Authority (ACPR)
Keynote Speech：The Prospects of Private Health Insurance Development in France
Mr. Bernard DELAS, a trained economist, has spent most of his professional career at the head of French insurance and bancassurance groups. Between 1971 and 1989, he held various positions at Samda, a subsidiary of Assurances Mutuelles Agricoles, before joining Groupama.
